# AWS Static Portfolio Website (S3 + CloudFront)

## ğŸ“Œ Project Overview

This project demonstrates how to host a **static portfolio website** on **Amazon S3** and deliver it globally using **Amazon CloudFront**. The setup follows industry best practices for **static website hosting, CDN usage, and HTTPS enablement**, making it suitable for learning and real-world DevOps fundamentals.

The website is built using **HTML and CSS**, version-controlled with **Git**, and deployed using **AWS services**.

---

## ğŸ¯ Objectives

* Build a personal static portfolio website
* Host the website using Amazon S3 static website hosting
* Configure public access securely using bucket policies
* Use Amazon CloudFront as a CDN for faster and secure delivery
* Enable HTTPS using CloudFront default TLS certificate
* Understand real-world cloud deployment workflow

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Tech Stack

* **Frontend**: HTML5, CSS3
* **Version Control**: Git, GitHub
* **Cloud Provider**: AWS
* **AWS Services Used**:

  * Amazon S3 (Static Website Hosting)
  * Amazon CloudFront (CDN)
  * AWS IAM (implicit usage via policies)

