## ğŸ§± Step-by-Step Implementation

### 1ï¸âƒ£ Website Development

* Created a responsive static portfolio using HTML and CSS
* Verified locally by opening `index.html` in a browser

### 2ï¸âƒ£ Version Control with Git

* Initialized a Git repository
* Committed source code
* Pushed code to GitHub

### 3ï¸âƒ£ Amazon S3 Setup

* Created an S3 bucket with a globally unique name
* Enabled **Static Website Hosting**
* Set `index.html` as the default root object
* Uploaded website files

### 4ï¸âƒ£ Bucket Policy Configuration

* Disabled **Block Public Access**
* Added bucket policy to allow public read (`s3:GetObject`)

### 5ï¸âƒ£ Website Verification

* Verified website using S3 website endpoint:

  ```
  http://<bucket-name>.s3-website.<region>.amazonaws.com
  ```

### 6ï¸âƒ£ Amazon CloudFront Configuration

* Created a CloudFront distribution
* Set S3 website endpoint as origin
* Enabled HTTP â†’ HTTPS redirection
* Used default CloudFront TLS certificate
* Disabled AWS WAF to avoid unnecessary costs

---

## ğŸ” Security Considerations

* HTTPS enabled via CloudFront TLS certificate
* No backend or sensitive data exposed
* Minimal permissions granted using bucket policies
* AWS WAF intentionally not enabled for cost efficiency

---

## ğŸ’° Cost Considerations

* Amazon S3: Free Tier eligible
* Amazon CloudFront: Pay-as-you-go (minimal usage)
* AWS WAF: Not enabled to avoid extra charges

